ll Flattening:<\/strong> Hedgehogs' quills act as natural flotation devices, providing them with buoyancy in water. They also have the unique ability to flatten their quills against their bodies, reducing resistance and aiding in smoother movement.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How Long Can a Hedgehog Swim For?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The duration of a hedgehog's swimming ability can vary depending on several factors, including its physical condition, energy level, and water temperature. Here are some considerations when it comes to the length of time a hedgehog can swim:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Stamina and Comfort<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Individual Variations:<\/strong> Each hedgehog has its own stamina and comfort level when it comes to swimming. Some hedgehogs may be more energetic and capable of swimming for longer periods, while others may prefer shorter swimming sessions.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Water Temperature:<\/strong> Cold water can cause hedgehogs to become hypothermic, so it's crucial to ensure the water temperature is suitable for their well-being. Warmer water may be more comfortable for them and allow for longer swimming durations.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>In general, hedgehogs are not built for extensive swimming and are more suited for short bursts of paddling. As responsible caretakers, it's important to monitor their swimming time, provide appropriate rest periods, and always prioritize their safety and comfort.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Can Hedgehog Swim More Than Once a Day?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Hedgehogs are not built for prolonged swimming sessions, and it is not typical for them to swim multiple times a day. Here are some factors to consider regarding hedgehogs and swimming frequency:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Physical Limitations<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Limited Stamina:<\/strong> Hedgehogs have limited stamina when it comes to swimming. Their bodies are not designe